Class Summary
Class Description
AudioController
The Audio Controller Class is responsible for setting audio at various points in the game.
BallController
The BallController abstract class provides a template that allows different types of Balls to be created.
BrickController
The BrickController abstract class provides a template that allows different types of Bricks to be created.
CementBrickModel
CementBrickModel Class extends BrickControllerClass to create the implementation of the CementBrickModel.
ClayBrickModel
ClayBrickModel Class extends BrickControllerClass creates the implementation of the ClayBrickModel.
CrackController
Crack Controller is responsible for providing the Bricks the 'Crack' Feature.
DebugPanelController
DebugPanelController Class extends JDialog and implements WindowListener.It is responsible for the functionality the Debug Panel.
DebugPanelView
DebugPanelView extends the JPanel to provide view of the Debug Panel
ExitButtonView
Implements the View of the ExitButton with ActionListener
FireBrickModel
FireBrickModel Class extends BrickController Class creates the implementation of the FireBrickModel.
GameBoardController
GameBoardView Class extends JComponent and implements KeyListener , MouseListener and MouseMotionListener to generate the GameBoard Functionality.
GameboardView
GameboardView is responsible to render the GameBoard View and Looks
GameFrameModel
GameFrameModel extends JFrame,which further implements WindowFocusListener,which takes care of the model of the game initialization.
HighScoreButtonView
Presents the View of the HighScore Button Updates Audio from the Audio Controller.
HighScoreController
HighScoreController is responsible the Score Functionality.
HighScoreModel
Responsible for creating the score model, shown during the game play.
HomeMenuView
Responsible for the HomeMenu View Implementation
IceBrickModel
IceBrickModel Class extends BrickController Class creates the implementation of the IceBrickModel.
InstructionButtonView
Implements the InstructionButtonView with the Implementation Updates Audio from the Audio Controller.
LevelModel
The LevelModel class creates levels for the Game.
Main
Main Method calls the GameFrameModel Class's initialize method
PauseMenuController
PauseMenuController is responsible for the PauseMenu Functionality in the GameBoard.
PauseMenuView
PauseMenuView is responsible for the view of the PauseMenu Screen
PlayerController
The PlayerController class is responsible for defining the Player's functionality.
PlayerModel
Responsible for defining the Player Model
RubberBallModel
RubberBallModel Class extends BallController Class creates the implementation of the RubberBall.
StartButtonView
StartButtonView is responsible for designing and rendering the StartButton.
SteelBrickModel
SteelBrickModel Class extends BrickControllerClass, creates the implementation of the SteelBrickModel.
TimerController
TimerController is responsible for controlling the timer functionality in the game
WallController
Responsible for implementing the Wall Functionality in the Game, with it's interaction with the ball, brick, player and the wall.
